org.hibernate.ogm.model.spi

Interface TupleSnapshot

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    AssociationRow, CouchDBTupleSnapshot, EmptyTupleSnapshot, InfinispanTupleSnapshot, MapTupleSnapshot, MongoDBTupleSnapshot, Neo4jTupleAssociationSnapshot, Neo4jTupleSnapshot

    public interface TupleSnapshot
    Represents a tuple snapshot as loaded by the datastore.

    This interface is to be implemented by dialects to avoid data duplication in memory (if possible), typically wrapping a store-specific representation of the tuple data. This snapshot will never be modified by the Hibernate OGM engine.

    Note that in the case of embeddables (e.g. composite ids), column names are given using dot notation, e.g. "id.countryCode" or "address.city.zipCode". The column names of the physical JPA model will be used, as e.g. given via @Column .

    In some special cases implementations may chose to persist different names than mandated by this model, e.g. always _id will be used as id column name by MongoDB. It is the responsibility of such implementation in this case to do the required translation of column names internally.

    Author:
    Emmanuel Bernard <emmanuel@hibernate.org>
